President Trump spoke with Parkland, Florida Mayor Christine Hunschofsky, Broward County Commissioner Michael Udine, and Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School Principal Ty Thompson to express condolences and offer support to the students, families, and community of Parkland. He thanked Mayor Hunschofsky for her leadership and dedication to the city and spoke with Commissioner Udine regarding the need to continue to help victims and their families. The President praised Principal Thompson for his resolve in helping students reach safety and his commitment to helping the community recover. President Trump commended the work of state and local officials, as well as law enforcement and first responders, and reiterated that the nation stands with Parkland.